Package com.pb.sawdust.util

Provides various utility classes.

See: Description

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    ContainsMetadata<K>
    The ContainsMetadata interface specifies that an implementing class contains metadata.
    Filter<I>
    The Filter interface provides a framework for filtering objects based on some standard.
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    AntiFilter<I>
    The AntiFilter provides a filter which is the opposite (inverse) of a given filter.
    Caster
    The Caster class provides convenience methods for casting between various types, primarily primitives.
    ClassInspector
    The ClassInspector class provides static methods for analyzing Class objects.
    ContainsMetadataImpl<K>
    The ContainsMetadataImpl provides a basic implementation of the ContainsMetadata interface, backed by a HashMap.
    Detokenizer
    The Detokenizer class provides very simple detokenizing (find key -> replace with value) operations on strings and files.
    EmptyFilter<T>
    The EmptyFilter is a filter which passes everything.
    FilterChain<I>
    The FilterChain class is used to combine many filters into a single, composite filter.
    MathUtil
    The MathUtil provides utility methods for dealing with numbers and math.
    MonteCarlo
    The MonteCarlo class provides the basic functionality for doing Monte Carlo choice analysis.
    MultiLock
    The MultiLock class provides a simple container for bundling multiple locks into a single entity.
    Pool<T>
    The Pool class is used to provide a container through which objects can be recycled.
    ProcessUtil
    The ProcessUtil provides convenience methods for running processes from Java.
    RandomDeluxe
    The RandomDeluxe class extends java.util.Random adding a variety of utility methods, including those for use this Strings and arrays.
    Range
    The Range class is used to create iterable integer sequences.
